@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token =

### ── AUTH ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register – Patient (public)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Test Patient",
  "email": "newpatient@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Patient123!",
  "dateOfBirth": "1995-03-20",
  "gender": "Male",
  "contactNumber": "555-0199",
  "address": "456 Oak Ave"
}

###

### Login – Admin (seed user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

###

### Login – Doctor (seed user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "doctor@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Doctor123!"
}

###

### Login – Receptionist (seed user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "reception@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Reception123!"
}

###

### Login – Patient (seed user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "patient@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Patient123!"
}

###

### Register Staff – Doctor  (requires Admin token in @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register/staff
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Dr. Sarah Lee",
  "email": "sarah.lee@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Doctor123!",
  "role": "Doctor",
  "specialization": "Neurology",
  "licenseNumber": "LIC-2024-002"
}

###

### Register Staff – Receptionist  (requires Admin token in @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register/staff
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Bob Green",
  "email": "bob.green@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Reception123!",
  "role": "Receptionist",
  "employeeId": "EMP-002"
}

###

### Register Staff – Admin  (requires Admin token in @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register/staff
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Super Admin",
  "email": "admin2@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Admin123!",
  "role": "Admin",
  "adminLevel": 2
}

### ── APPOINTMENTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### After logging in (above), set @token to the returned JWT.
### Fill these in with real GUIDs from your DB (or copy from a booking response).

@appointmentId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@doctorId      = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@patientId     = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### Book appointment – Patient (PatientId is ignored; taken from JWT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "appointmentDate": "2026-05-15",
  "timeSlot": "10:00:00",
  "visitType": "GeneralConsultation"
}

###

### Book appointment – Receptionist / Admin (PatientId required)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "patientId": "{{patientId}}",
  "doctorId": "{{doctorId}}",
  "appointmentDate": "2026-05-15",
  "timeSlot": "10:20:00",
  "visitType": "FollowUp"
}

###

### Get my appointments – Patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/my
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get appointment by id – any authenticated role (filtered server-side)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get appointments for a patient – Doctor / Receptionist / Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/patient/{{patientId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get doctor schedule (full) – Doctor / Receptionist / Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/doctor/{{doctorId}}/schedule
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get doctor schedule – daily view (?from=&to= same date)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/doctor/{{doctorId}}/schedule?from=2026-05-15&to=2026-05-15
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get doctor schedule – weekly view
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/doctor/{{doctorId}}/schedule?from=2026-05-11&to=2026-05-17
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Cancel appointment (no reason) – Patient (own) / Receptionist / Admin
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Cancel appointment with reason
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "reason": "Patient feeling better, no longer needs the visit."
}

###

### Confirm appointment – Doctor (assigned) / Receptionist / Admin
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "newStatus": "Confirmed"
}

###

### Mark appointment Completed – Doctor (assigned) / Receptionist / Admin
###   Allowed only from Confirmed. Sets PaymentStatus to Charged.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "newStatus": "Completed"
}

###

### Mark appointment NoShow – Doctor (assigned) / Receptionist / Admin
###   Allowed only from Confirmed. Sets PaymentStatus to Charged.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "newStatus": "NoShow"
}

### ── MEDICAL RECORDS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### Set @token to a Doctor JWT for write requests, or a Patient JWT to test
### the ownership rules. @patientId and @doctorId are shared from above.

@recordId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### Get patient's medical record – Doctor (any patient) or Patient (own only; 403 otherwise)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/{{patientId}}/records
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Create medical record – Doctor only (409 if a record already exists for this patient)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/{{patientId}}/records
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "diagnosis": "Hypertension stage 1",
  "treatmentPlan": "Low-sodium diet, daily 30-min walk, follow up in 3 months."
}

###

### Update medical record – Doctor only
###   Replace @recordId with the id returned from the create call above.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/records/{{recordId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "diagnosis": "Hypertension stage 1 — improving",
  "treatmentPlan": "Continue diet; reduce medication to maintenance dose."
}

###

### Get prescriptions for a record – Doctor or Patient-own (403 otherwise)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/records/{{recordId}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Add prescription to a record – Doctor only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/records/{{recordId}}/prescriptions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "medicationName": "Lisinopril",
  "dosage": "10mg once daily",
  "instructions": "Take in the morning with water. Avoid potassium supplements.",
  "issueDate": "2026-05-11"
}

###

### Add lab result for a patient – Doctor only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/{{patientId}}/lab-results
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "testName": "Complete Blood Count (CBC)",
  "resultValue": "WBC 6.2, RBC 4.8, HGB 14.1, PLT 230 — all within normal range",
  "resultDate": "2026-05-11"
}

###

### Get lab results for a patient – Doctor or Patient-own (403 otherwise)
###   Results are ordered newest ResultDate first.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patients/{{patientId}}/lab-results
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── VISIT SUMMARY ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### Patient submits, Patient (own) and Doctor (assigned) can read.
### Receptionist/Admin are blocked. Non-owner Patient and non-assigned Doctor
### both receive 403 — including when the appointment id does not exist
### (intentional, to prevent appointment-id enumeration).

### Submit visit summary – Patient only (own appointment)
###   400 if status is Completed/Cancelled.
###   409 if a summary already exists for this appointment.
###   403 if the appointment is not yours (or does not exist).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/summary
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "symptoms": "Persistent headache and mild nausea for the past 3 days.",
  "description": "Pain is concentrated on the right side, worsens with bright light.",
  "painLevel": 6,
  "symptomDuration": "3 days"
}

###

### Get visit summary – Patient (own) or Doctor (assigned)
###   403 if the appointment is not yours / not assigned to you / does not exist.
###   400 if the appointment is yours but no summary has been submitted.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/appointments/{{appointmentId}}/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── EMERGENCY ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### Patient-only endpoints. Token must belong to a Patient role.
### POST /request  — stores coordinates, creates EmergencyRequest (Pending),
###                  returns top-3 nearest clinics by Haversine distance.
### GET  /nearby-clinics — read-only lookup; coordinates NOT persisted,
###                        but the call IS logged for accountability.

### Submit emergency request – Patient only
###   409 if patient already has a Pending request.
###   400 if patient account is blocked.
###   Body coordinates are the only place location is ever captured.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/emergency/request
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "latitude": 31.9869,
  "longitude": 35.8969
}

###

### Get nearby clinics – Patient only (coordinates as query params)
###   Returns ALL clinics sorted by Haversine distance, nearest first.
###   Coordinates are NOT stored; call is logged with PatientId + timestamp.
###   400 if lat/lng are out of valid geographic range.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/emergency/nearby-clinics?lat=31.9869&lng=35.8969
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get active emergencies – Doctor / Receptionist / Admin only
###   Returns all Pending and Dispatched requests, oldest first.
###   Empty list (not 404) when there are no active emergencies.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/emergency/active
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update emergency status – Doctor / Receptionist / Admin only
###   Valid transitions: Pending→Dispatched (1), Dispatched→Resolved (2).
###   All other transitions return 400. NewStatus 0 (Pending) is rejected by validation.
###   Replace {{emergencyId}} with the Guid returned when the request was created.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/emergency/{{emergencyId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "newStatus": 1
}

### ── ADMIN – USER MANAGEMENT ────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### All endpoints require an Admin token.
###
### GET  /users?role=      — list all users; optional filter by role (Admin/Doctor/Receptionist/Patient)
### POST /users            — create Doctor or Receptionist account (Patient creation is not allowed here)
### PUT  /users/{id}       — update any user's info (only supplied fields are changed)
### DELETE /users/{id}     — deactivate account (sets AccountStatus=Blocked); never hard-deletes

### List all users – Admin only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### List users filtered by role
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users?role=Doctor
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Create Doctor account – Admin only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Dr. Sara Ahmed",
  "email": "sara.ahmed@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Doctor123!",
  "role": "Doctor",
  "specialization": "Cardiology",
  "licenseNumber": "JO-DOC-2024-999"
}

###

### Create Receptionist account – Admin only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Rami Khalil",
  "email": "rami.khalil@smartcare.com",
  "password": "Staff123!",
  "role": "Receptionist",
  "employeeId": "EMP-0042"
}

###

### Update user info – Admin only (only provided fields are changed)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "fullName": "Dr. Sara Ahmed-Hassan",
  "specialization": "Interventional Cardiology"
}

###

### Deactivate user – Admin only (sets AccountStatus=Blocked; no hard delete)
###   400 if user is already deactivated.
###   400 if admin tries to deactivate their own account.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ── ADMIN – SYSTEM SETTINGS ────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### All endpoints require an Admin token.
### Values are always strings in storage; numeric settings are stored as "30" etc.
### Default settings seeded on startup: NoShowFee, GeneralConsultationDuration,
###   FollowUpDuration, AnnualCheckupDuration.
### PUT rejects unknown keys with 400 — only existing settings can be updated.

### List all settings
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/settings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update a setting
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/settings
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "key": "NoShowFee",
  "value": "10"
}

###

### ── ADMIN – REPORTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### All endpoints require an Admin token.
### Both date filters are optional; omit to query all time.
### 400 if startDate > endDate.

### Appointment report – totals + per-doctor breakdown
###   Summary: total, completed, noShows, cancelled, pending, confirmed
###   ByDoctor: same counters per doctor, ordered by total desc
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/reports/appointments?startDate=2026-05-01&endDate=2026-05-31
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Appointment report – all time (no date filter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/reports/appointments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Visit frequency – daily booking count for a date range
###   Counts all non-cancelled appointments grouped by date, ordered ascending.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/reports/visits?startDate=2026-05-01&endDate=2026-05-31
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Visit frequency – all time
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/reports/visits
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
